view_template in a Spina CMS Rails app there is an option of exclude_from that will take an array of strings. For any resources included in this array, that view template will not be available to pages of that resource.
theme.view_templates = [
  {
    # The rest of your view template...
    exclude_from: ["main", "blog_resource"]
  }
]
Note: If you want to exclude templates from being used on main spina pages, you can just exclude from the implicit "main" resource.

